### OAuth2 Device Flow -> protected /whoami call
# This file demonstrates the full device authorization flow:
# 1) Device client asks for a device_code/user_code.
# 2) Human user opens verification URL and authenticates/consents.
# 3) Device client polls /oauth2/token until access token is issued.
# 4) Access token is used to call resource server /whoami.
#
# Prerequisites:
# 1) Start auth server: ./mvnw -pl oauth/auth-server spring-boot:run
# 2) Start resource server: ./mvnw -pl oauth/quotes-protected-resource spring-boot:run
# 3) Auth server must have a client registered for device flow (device_code grant type).

@authServer = http://localhost:9090
@resourceServer = http://localhost:8081
@client_id = device-client
@client_secret = device-client-secret
@scope = quotes.read

### Step 0 (negative case): Call protected endpoint without an access token.
### Expected result: 401 Unauthorized from the resource server.
GET {{resourceServer}}/whoami
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 1: Request device and user codes from the authorization server.
### Response should include: device_code, user_code, verification_uri, and interval.
POST {{authServer}}/oauth2/device_authorization
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Accept: application/json

client_id={{client_id}}&client_secret={{client_secret}}&scope={{scope}}

> {%
  client.global.set("device_code", response.body.device_code);
  client.global.set("user_code", response.body.user_code);
  client.global.set("verification_uri", response.body.verification_uri);
  client.global.set("verification_uri_complete", response.body.verification_uri_complete);
  client.global.set("poll_interval", response.body.interval);
%}

###

### Step 2: Open verification page in browser.
### Log in (ex: user/user). This sample's device client is configured without consent prompts.
### If verification_uri_complete is returned, opening it pre-fills the user code.
### Do not use the IntelliJ HTTP response body itself as completion; you must complete browser login.
GET {{verification_uri_complete}}
Accept: text/html

###

### Step 3: Poll token endpoint until access token is returned.
### If user has not completed verification yet, response may be authorization_pending.
### If you receive access_denied, start over from Step 1 to get a fresh device_code.
POST {{authServer}}/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Accept: application/json

grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:device_code&device_code={{device_code}}&client_id={{client_id}}&client_secret={{client_secret}}

> {%
  if (response.body.access_token) {
    client.global.set("access_token", response.body.access_token);
  }
%}

###

### Step 4: Call protected endpoint using the issued Bearer token.
GET {{resourceServer}}/whoami
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Accept: application/json
